<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870121-0167 </DOCNO><HL> Corrections andamp; Amplifications:Scientific Measurement Systems Inc.</HL><DD> 01/21/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> SCMS WNEWS </IN><TEXT>   SCIENTIFIC MEASUREMENT SYSTEMS INC. said its decision to appoint an independent counsel to investigate allegations of insider trading, among other things, was made prior to a state court hearing last week. An earlier edition indicated the appointment was the result of the court hearing.    (See: &quot;Scientific Measurement Agrees to an Inquiry of Holder's Allegations&quot; -- WSJ Jan. 19, 1987) </TEXT></DOC>